  "prompt": "What's the cleanest diet possible?",
  "response": "A clean diet typically focuses on whole, minimally processed foods that provide essential nutrients while avoiding additives, preservatives, and artificial ingredients. Here are some key principles:\n\n1. Whole Foods\n- Fresh fruits and vegetables\n- Lean proteins\n- Whole grains\n- Nuts and seeds\n- Legumes\n\n2. Protein Sources\n- Wild-caught fish\n- Organic, grass-fed meats\n- Free-range poultry\n- Plant-based proteins (beans, lentils)\n\n3. Avoid\n- Processed foods\n- Added sugars\n- Artificial sweeteners\n- Refined carbohydrates\n- Trans fats\n- Excessive sodium\n\n4. Additional Guidelines\n- Organic produce when possible\n- Locally sourced foods\n- Minimal cooking methods (steaming, grilling)\n- Drink plenty of water\n- Limit alcohol consumption\n\n5. Optional Approaches\n- Mediterranean diet\n- Plant-based diet\n- Whole30 diet\n- Paleo diet\n\nThe \"cleanest\" diet can vary based on individual health needs, but generally emphasizes whole, nutrient-dense foods with minimal processing and additives.\n\nConsulting a nutritionist can help personalize a clean diet plan tailored to your specific health goals and requirements.",
